			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hehehe... this always confuses people. There are two Grimrots. One is in the ruins area near the bridge to North Karana, and he's about level 20. Kill him and you get nothing of value. Also, I don't know if he is the one you need for the head quest, but it's possible both work. The other form is near the pyramid, I believe to the southeast of the zone. He's MUCH harder, a level 36 or so plate-covered shadowknight, with a well rounded package, including powerful DoTs, a NASTY melee, and a plethora or harm touches for your dying pleasure. This is the guy that drops the Opal Scythe. Take it to Camlend Serbold for a NICE item. (I've gotten combines, a paladin-only tunic, not Valorium, though. :[ And of course, the ever impressive large lantern. hehe)
				</font>
